metadata.description: Ultra Full emergency dataset: detailed schema, province-level entries for some countries, 80+ categories supported. Populated with real, commonly-known emergency numbers for major countries and realistic placeholders elsewhere. THIS DATA SHOULD BE VERIFIED AGAINST OFFICIAL GOVERNMENT SOURCES BEFORE PRODUCTION USE.

rescue_and_disaster.coast_guard: US Coast Guard: 911 or 1-800-424-8802 (report pollution/maritime emergencies)

rescue_and_disaster.disaster_management: National Disaster Response Force (NDRF): 011-24121555 (varies by region)
rescue_and_disaster.coast_guard: 1913 (Maritime Rescue/Indian Coast Guard regional numbers vary)

health_and_safety.mental_health: Talk Suicide Canada - provincial numbers vary

rescue_and_disaster.coast_guard: Canadian Coast Guard: regional numbers vary

health_and_safety.sexual_assault: Rape Crisis England & Wales / local services

rescue_and_disaster.coast_guard: 999 (ask for Coastguard) or 01202 338 000 (Maritime & Coastguard Agency switchboard)

rescue_and_disaster.disaster_management: State-based SES / AFAC / 132500 (SES in some states)

health_and_safety.poison_control: 030 19240 (Poison Information Center Berlin) - regional numbers vary
